      <exercise>
        <statement>
          <p>
            The next week it starts snowing again, at possibly a different rate from last week.  Once again I set off at <m>8</m>am, and travel <m></m> miles by <m>9</m>am, and an additional <m>3</m> miles an hour later.  What time did it start to snow this week?
          </p>
        </statement>
        <answer>
          <p>
            <m>g(x)=f(-x)</m>. So, we can reflect the graph of <m>y=f(x)</m> across the <m>y</m>-axis to obtain <m>y=g(x)</m>.
